<div id="review_872003321" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/872003321" />
    <a title="Pink" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/14084605-pink"><img alt="Pink" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1366445251p2/14084605.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/872003321?book_show_action=true">Sep 18, 2016</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Pink" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Pink" href="/user/show/14084605-pink">Pink</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780007247202" href="/book/show/1411036.The_Golden_Notebook">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer872003321" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5350947696204530088">I have to give this five huge stars. Even though I had problems with the last few chapters, this was never a chore to get through. I looked forward to reading it each day and enjoyed each of the notebooks, as different as they were. This is a feminist novel in as much as it&apos;s about female characters and their sexual relationships, but it&apos;s more of a look at mental breakdown, in a post war, communist party era. Masterful writing, as expected from Lessing and highly recommended. </span>
  <span id="freeText5350947696204530088" style="display:none">I have to give this five huge stars. Even though I had problems with the last few chapters, this was never a chore to get through. I looked forward to reading it each day and enjoyed each of the notebooks, as different as they were. This is a feminist novel in as much as it's about female characters and their sexual relationships, but it's more of a look at mental breakdown, in a post war, communist party era. Masterful writing, as expected from Lessing and highly recommended. </span>
  <a data-text-id="5350947696204530088" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

